sentences.english: If I overslept because I am ill, I always call in absent to work –
sentences.chinese: 如果我睡过头是因为我生病了，我总会打电话请假。

sentences.english: Bias affects the overshoot or undershoot of the motion through the keyframe.
sentences.chinese: 偏见影响过头或欠该议案通过关键帧。

sentences.english: What if she oversleeps and misses the bus?
sentences.chinese: 假如她睡过头错过班车怎么办？

sentences.english: Looking back on it, I wish we hadn t been given in so easily.
sentences.chinese: 回过头来看，我希望我们没有这样轻易让步。

sentences.english: "I love the West, " she said. Her eyes were shining softly. She looked away and out the train window.
sentences.chinese: 她说，两眼流露着柔柔的光，撇过头望车窗的外面。

sentences.english: It is definitely possible to over do it.
sentences.chinese: 这是绝对有可能做过头的事。

sentences.english: We will come back to this point later in this article.
sentences.chinese: 在本文后面，我们将回过头来讨论这一点。

sentences.english: Hopefully you don't give us too much of a good thing.
sentences.chinese: 对于这样的好事，万分希望您别让我们好过头。

sentences.english: If you also oversleep, we'll go to the next station.
sentences.chinese: 如果你也睡过头，我们就到下一战下车。

sentences.english: Too much of a good thing.
She was afraid of oversleeping, so she asked someone to wake her up.
sentences.chinese: 她担心睡过头，于是请人叫醒她。

sentences.english: If you don't set your alarm clock, you'll oversleep.
sentences.chinese: 如果你不设闹钟，就会睡过头。

sentences.english: He is afraid of waking up late, so he always has an alarm on his bedside table.
sentences.chinese: 他怕睡过头，总是在床头小几上放一个闹钟。

sentences.english: He, turned his head and looked at her over his shoulder.
sentences.chinese: 这时他回过头来望着她。

sentences.english: Boy, I'm kind of tuckered out. How are you feeling, Elizabeth?
sentences.chinese: 我有点累过头了，伊丽莎白，你怎样？

sentences.english: The girl turned her face and wept.
